# AI Museum Curator — Greek Mythology Edition

An interactive Streamlit app that fetches artwork metadata from The Metropolitan Museum of Art (MET) and uses optional OpenAI models to generate museum-style curator explanations. Includes a hierarchical genealogy of Greek mythology (Mythic Lineages).

## Features
- Browse Greek deities and fetch **real** MET artworks (only artworks with downloadable images are shown).
- Works & Analysis: left–right layout with a large image and a structured information panel (Object Info + About + AI sections).
- Interactive Art Zone: visual-detail questions, sketch/style analyzer, myth identifier, archetype quiz, and optional image generation (OpenAI).
- Mythic Lineages: hierarchical family tree (Graphviz) from primordial gods to heroes.
- Data Source: MET Museum Open API.

